Meet <b>Star</b>, our citizen of the week!<br><br>Star lives at <a href='/home/?user=bubbles4121'>26423 Summer Street</a>, in the beautiful and peaceful neighborhood of Golden Valley.  She's been a citizen since December 21st of 2004, and absolutely loves her new home.<br><br>Star is a very caring young lady, whose friends describe her as flexible and easy to get along with, as well as obsessed with sports.  Star is interested in a wide variety of athletic pursuits, ranging from hockey to martial arts, and is quite good at them all!  She's already received several trophies from Millsberry Academy for her excellence in Sherman Home Run Derby, Sink the Three, and Rope Race.<br><br>After school and on the weekends, if there is a big game going on, Star is sure to be there, cheering her team on (that is, if she's not in the game herself).  Whether it's a football game, soccer match, or even a baseball game, everyone knows that Star will be there, yelling and rooting for her team until she's hoarse.  Star is easy to spot, because she often wears clothes that are green, light blue, or dark blue, since those are her favorite colors.<br><br>On evenings when she isn't attending a sporting event, Star loves to sit outside with her headphones on, listening to country, rhythm & blues, or jazz as she gazes at the stars.  She finds both activities very relaxing, as astronomy is one of her favorite subjects.  Her friends are always impressed by the number of constellations she knows, and enjoy sitting outside with her while she points out the groups of stars to them.<br><br>Congratulations Star, you've truly earned your place as citizen of the week!</div>
